summary.para: The ApiFileHandler class is used to create the Java Script API (.js) file. The JS API can have "<%# XX.YY %>" tags that is replaced by the return value of the property YY of class/instance XX in the Metadata. The substitution is done using Metadata.GetFunctionName(XX.YY). The JavScript API can also contain "ifdef"-like statements to remove code from earlier versions of the API.

#APINEW X.Y ... code #ENDAPI
the X.Y is the version where the new functionality is added.

The code can also contain tags for code that is removed from a specific version and forward (deprecated code).
#APIREMOVE X.Y ... code #ENDAPI

member.name: M:Spotfire.Dxp.Web.InternalDocumentCacheEntry.CloningFinished(System.Boolean)
member.summary:
This method should be called when a calling cloner has finished its work. The method releases the thread lock on this object, for example Informs waiting threads that it is now OK to start working with this instance. It also decreases the counter for pending clones.
If the property
is not set when this method is called, the next thread accessing the object should not wait for the property to be set. Instead interrupt the wait and let that second thread try to set the property.
If false the nr of instances that has cloned this template will be decreased.
